# Problem

Prove

\\[\cos(x)<\cos^4\left(\frac{x}{2}\right),\forall x\in\left(0,\frac{\pi}{2}\right).\\]

<!-- SOLUTION_START -->
# Solution

Use the half-angle formula to get

\\[\cos(x)<\left(\frac{1+\cos(x)}{2}\right)^2.\]

Simplification gives

\\[(1-\cos^2(x))^2>0\\]

which is true when $$x\in\left(0,\frac{\pi}{2}\right)$$.